                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350511-1326-offence-1 t18350511-name-1260"></join>James Dawson</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350511-name-1261" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1261" type="surname" value="DAWSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1261" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES DAWSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a carpenter. On the 20th of April I was at Greenwich fair—I felt my handkerchief taken from my coat pocket, while I was in a crowd near Richardson's show—that was knocked off pur-</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183505110207"></xptr>
               <p>posely at the time, and then my pocket-picked—my arms were pinioned, but I turned my head round, and the officer had got hold of the prisoner—he asked me if that was my handkerchief; I instantly laid it was, and seized hold of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350511-name-1262" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1262" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1262" type="surname" value="REARDON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350511-name-1262" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>DANIEL REARDON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. I was at the fair—I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket—he was alone—I had seen him in the fair before, and watched him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you see me knock his hat off? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; I took the handkerchief from his hand, and secured him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I and another young man went to the fair to sell four hundred oranges—I took a walk through the fair to have a look at it—I saw two Young lads, one of them had a handkerchief in hit hand; the other said, "D—n that old thing, go and fetch us a <hi rend="italic">tanner"</hi>—he threw it down; I took it up—the policeman said, "Give us that handkerchief"—I said, "I shall not"—I did not know he was a policeman; he was in plain clothes—if I had given it to him, he would have said nothing about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18350511-1326-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
